I don't want to go back to the dormitory.

570
00:24:35,520 --> 00:24:36,720
You have to.

571
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:39,520
Don't you know what they all say?

572
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:42,680
If you live together before getting married, 
 you'll soon be tired of each other.

573
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:45,280
These couples usually break up before getting married.

574
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:48,240
Who said it?

575
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:50,080
It's just how the saying goes.

576
00:24:50,720 --> 00:24:51,760
Who is the saying?

577
00:24:51,760 --> 00:24:52,680
I don't know him.

578
00:24:53,240 --> 00:24:54,440
I don't care. I'm going to sleep.

579
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:56,800
Stop it.

580
00:24:58,880 --> 00:24:59,640
Come on.

581
00:25:03,080 --> 00:25:04,840
I have ironed your clothes.

582
00:25:05,240 --> 00:25:06,000
Take a shower

583
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:07,360
and come back here next week.

584
00:25:07,360 --> 00:25:08,520
Just one night.

585
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:10,840
Come on, it's just one night.

586
00:25:11,120 --> 00:25:12,400
No.

587
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:14,560
One night will become one month.

588
00:25:14,560 --> 00:25:16,160
And then it will go on to one year.

589
00:25:16,570 --> 00:25:18,960
We can have our whole life together after marriage.

590
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:20,470
We can afford to not stay together tonight.

591
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:24,520
Come on.

592
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:28,760
Go now.

593
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:32,480
Are you going or not?

594
00:25:43,720 --> 00:25:44,920
Sister.

595
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,800
Why are you looking at me so suspiciously?

596
00:25:56,680 --> 00:25:57,640
Dear sister,

597
00:25:58,040 --> 00:26:00,080
do you have 50,000 euros?

598
00:26:01,840 --> 00:26:02,760
What do you want?

599
00:26:04,760 --> 00:26:06,120
A friend of mine

600
00:26:06,120 --> 00:26:07,680
is doing fundraising for a restaurant.

601
00:26:07,680 --> 00:26:09,440
She wants me to be a shareholder.

602
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:10,680
Did you invest?

603
00:26:11,120 --> 00:26:11,920
I am planning to.

604
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:15,160
Opening a restaurant is way less profitable than 
 investing in stocks.

605
00:26:15,160 --> 00:26:17,200
But investing in stocks is way less fun.

606
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:18,520
Also,

607
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:20,400
I have no idea how to play the stock market.

608
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:23,160
Do you have money?

609
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:24,640
No.

610
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,680
You say it with such confidence.

611
00:26:28,360 --> 00:26:29,960
Then why are you making these plans?

612
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:33,920
I want you to join it.

613
00:26:35,880 --> 00:26:37,960
Come on, mind your own business.

614
00:26:40,320 --> 00:26:43,480
Exactly, life should be a vibrant business.

615
00:26:44,880 --> 00:26:46,240
Should I live my life like you?

616
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:47,520
Check yourself.

617
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:49,040
I can see continence from your face.

618
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:50,400
You're already in old lady mode.

619
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:52,320
What's the point of living a life like this?

620
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:54,800
Suppose there's no point, should I suicide?

621
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:55,560
I didn't mean that.

622
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:57,360
What I mean

623
00:26:57,360 --> 00:27:00,120
is you should make your life more interesting.

624
00:27:03,930 --> 00:27:05,640
How do you define an interesting life?

625
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:08,160
Opening a restaurant.

626
00:27:08,680 --> 00:27:10,960
I'm not business material.

627
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:12,120
I forbid your self-denial.

628
00:27:12,120 --> 00:27:13,640
You went abroad for graduate studies.

629
00:27:13,640 --> 00:27:16,000
It's proof that you're so much cleverer than me.

630
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:17,000
It's not the same.

631
00:27:18,390 --> 00:27:19,920
But I don't think that's what matters.

632
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:21,200
The problem is

633
00:27:21,200 --> 00:27:21,920
you're lazy.

634
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:25,440
Congratulations on getting it right.

635
00:27:25,440 --> 00:27:26,840
I am lazy.

636
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:29,280
It's tiring to open a restaurant and make a profit.

637
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:30,600
You have to be diligent.

638
00:27:30,600 --> 00:27:32,160
I can never do that.

639
00:27:33,520 --> 00:27:35,320
It's such a big world.

640
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:37,880
Just get out of bed and experience more, sister.

641
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:39,320
What do you want me to experience?

642
00:27:40,840 --> 00:27:41,840
I do not believe

643
00:27:41,840 --> 00:27:43,960
a bunch of women can run a restaurant well.

644
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:47,400
I can't just throw away that money.

645
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:49,440
After all,

646
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:51,720
I spent five years earning it when I was young.

647
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:54,600
Then it's another reason why you shouldn't 
 put it in the bank.

648
00:27:55,040 --> 00:27:56,040
Can you bear seeing it

649
00:27:56,040 --> 00:27:57,920
devaluating every day?

650
00:27:59,440 --> 00:28:01,000
Don't you think about my money!

651
00:28:01,520 --> 00:28:02,800
But I won't waste it.

652
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:03,560
It's an investment.

653
00:28:03,560 --> 00:28:05,080
Money begets money.

654
00:28:05,080 --> 00:28:06,160
You only have 50,000 euros.

655
00:28:06,160 --> 00:28:07,800
It's not enough for the rest of your life, right?

656
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:09,400
You're such a miser.

657
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:12,760
What's wrong with being a miser?

658
00:28:13,360 --> 00:28:14,640
At least I can keep the money.

659
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:16,400
It's always better than if you can't keep it.

660
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:19,240
I have no relatives and I live under other's roofs.

661
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:20,720
If I waste that money,

662
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:22,400
I'll have to kill myself.

663
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:24,240
You won't end up like that.

664
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:25,640
Nothing you say will change my mind.

665
00:28:25,640 --> 00:28:27,200
I told you I'm not investing and I won't.

666
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:35,000
How about this?

667
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:36,000
Lend me the money.

668
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:36,600
No.

669
00:28:38,120 --> 00:28:39,640
I will pay interest.

670
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:41,840
I will pay more than the banks pay you.

671
00:28:42,520 --> 00:28:43,920
How about 15 percent?

672
00:28:47,510 --> 00:28:48,720
If you don't lend me the money,

673
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:50,480
I will ask the bank for a loan.

674
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:51,720
Their interest rate is lower.

675
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:56,040
How much do you want?

676
00:28:58,720 --> 00:28:59,590
300,000 RMB.

677
00:28:59,590 --> 00:29:01,040
I'll pay you back in one year.

678
00:29:01,040 --> 00:29:03,000
Interest included, how much is it?

679
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:04,200
345,000 RMB.

680
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:08,040
You're brilliant.

681
00:29:09,040 --> 00:29:10,400
What if you can't pay me back?

682
00:29:12,320 --> 00:29:14,160
I will sell the house and get the money.

683
00:29:15,560 --> 00:29:17,440
A statement doesn't count as a binding contract.

684
00:29:17,440 --> 00:29:19,760
I hereby offer an IOU.

685
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:28,560
What are these that you got?

686
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:30,560
New skincare products.

687
00:29:30,560 --> 00:29:32,200
It's a whole set of INGLEMIREPHARM'S products.

688
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:33,920
I heard it's an activating product

689
00:29:33,920 --> 00:29:35,220
that helps brighten the skin.

690
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:37,520
I think I should treat myself better

691
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:39,560
and be positive in life.

692
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:42,640
You should've done that a long time ago.

693
00:29:43,160 --> 00:29:44,520
When the restaurant is open

694
00:29:44,520 --> 00:29:46,520
and you stand in front of it,

695
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:48,400
people will think it's a salon

696
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:49,920
if they don't know it's a restaurant.

697
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:51,480
Your skin is luminous.

698
00:29:53,120 --> 00:29:54,720
It's time to talk about some serious stuff.

699
00:29:54,910 --> 00:29:56,720
We have to decide the name of our restaurant.

700
00:29:56,720 --> 00:29:57,920
I need to register it.

701
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:03,560
All shareholders are women.

702
00:30:03,560 --> 00:30:04,880
How about "Women's Session"?

703
00:30:04,880 --> 00:30:05,480
There you go.

704
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:07,360
It really sounds like a salon.

705
00:30:07,360 --> 00:30:08,500
Or a postpartum care center,

706
00:30:08,500 --> 00:30:09,040
if not a salon.

707
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:10,200
We'll take the naming job from you.

708
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:12,120
What on earth was the name you came up with?

709
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:13,240
Bao Xue, give us an idea.

710
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:15,360
Don't make me do it.

711
00:30:15,360 --> 00:30:16,040
OK?

712
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:17,880
I really can't think of anything.

713
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:18,760
Opening a restaurant

714
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:20,720
is too far away from my ideal of becoming

715
00:30:20,720 --> 00:30:22,800
a performance artist.

716
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:24,480
It's like walking at an intersection.

717
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:27,120
I really have no idea at all.

718
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:35,160
Let's call it Intersection Bistro.

719
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:36,480
How about that?

720
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:39,000
Intersection Bistro.

721
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:40,680
Intersection Bistro.

722
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:41,920
To put it simply,

723
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:43,160
the name means

724
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:45,000
that we do dishes of all places.

725
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:46,960
But if you think more about it,

726
00:30:47,280 --> 00:30:48,480
in many cases,

727
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:49,400
the ways of life

728
00:30:49,400 --> 00:30:50,720
women choose in the beginning

729
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:53,220
are almost always completely different from 
 the lives we live.

730
00:30:53,220 --> 00:30:55,200
It's just like going the wrong way in an intersection.

731
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:56,440
That's quite deep.

732
00:30:56,650 --> 00:30:57,760
But Intersection Bistro

733
00:30:57,760 --> 00:30:59,680
doesn't really sound like a restaurant.

734
00:30:59,680 --> 00:31:02,470
At least it's better than names like 
 House of Happiness, Fortune or Spring.

735
00:31:02,470 --> 00:31:03,430
It's just my idea.

736
00:31:03,430 --> 00:31:04,760
We can think of something else.

737
00:31:04,760 --> 00:31:06,120
Intersection Bistro.

738
00:31:06,120 --> 00:31:08,360
But the word intersection

739
00:31:08,360 --> 00:31:10,160
feels a bit internal and not appealing.

740
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:12,200
How about we call it

741
00:31:12,840 --> 00:31:14,120
Crossroad Bistro?

742
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:16,320
Crossroad Bistro.

743
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:17,600
It's a bit weird.

744
00:31:18,400 --> 00:31:18,880
Weird?

745
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:20,720
I think it's okay to sound weird.

746
00:31:21,320 --> 00:31:23,280
People remember weird names better.

747
00:31:23,280 --> 00:31:25,520
Crossroad Bistro.

748
00:31:26,120 --> 00:31:27,360
I think it will work.

749
00:31:28,080 --> 00:31:29,400
Crossroad Bistro, it is.

750
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:31,680
Let's vote.

751
00:31:33,520 --> 00:31:33,960
OK.

752
00:31:33,960 --> 00:31:34,880
Alright, come on.

753
00:31:34,880 --> 00:31:36,310
Give me your identity cards

754
00:31:36,310 --> 00:31:38,360
and transfer the investment to the account I gave you.

755
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:39,960
I have prepared these a long time ago.

756
00:31:39,960 --> 00:31:41,600
I even stole my sister's identity card.

757
00:31:41,600 --> 00:31:42,360
Be quick.

758
00:31:42,360 --> 00:31:42,880
OK.

759
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:45,160
Are you sure your sister won't call the police 
 and arrest you?

760
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:46,000
I am most certain.

761
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:47,240
I know her well.

762
00:31:47,760 --> 00:31:49,200
She won't do that.

763
00:31:52,520 --> 00:31:53,600
Aunt.

764
00:31:53,600 --> 00:31:54,200
You're back.

765
00:31:54,200 --> 00:31:55,200
Grandpa.

766
00:31:59,000 --> 00:31:59,520
Sister.

767
00:31:59,520 --> 00:32:00,160
Come over.

768
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:01,480
I need to show you something.

769
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:06,720
What is it?

770
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:08,360
Come here.

771
00:32:19,080 --> 00:32:20,200
Congratulations.

772
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:22,000
You have a business now.

773
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:23,120
The same goes for you.

774
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:24,280
Congratulations.

775
00:32:28,230 --> 00:32:30,560
Did you make me a shareholder with the money I lent you?

776
00:32:30,560 --> 00:32:31,400
What do you think?

777
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:32,920
Isn't it a pleasant surprise?

778
00:32:33,440 --> 00:32:35,200
Did you ask for my approval?

779
00:32:35,200 --> 00:32:36,000
I did.

780
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:36,960
You refused.

781
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:38,740
Then why did you do it knowing that I disagree?

782
00:32:39,600 --> 00:32:40,320
Sister.

783
00:32:40,320 --> 00:32:41,920
This is a great chance

784
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:43,720
to earn money and support yourself.

785
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:45,840
Others can't get this chance at all even if they try hard.

786
00:32:46,040 --> 00:32:47,400
I pulled some strings

787
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:49,080
to get the chance for you.

788
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:50,480
But I don't want this.

789
00:32:50,480 --> 00:32:51,200
I'm telling you.

790
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:52,200
Get me out of this right now

791
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:53,290
and give me my money back.

792
00:32:53,290 --> 00:32:54,080
Take it easy.

793
00:32:54,080 --> 00:32:55,880
Listen to me, okay?

794
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:57,440
If we earn money from the restaurant,

795
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:59,000
you can have the shares.

796
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,160
If we lose money,

797
00:33:01,080 --> 00:33:01,960
the shares are mine.

798
00:33:01,960 --> 00:33:02,600
One year later,

799
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:03,640
I will pay you back in full

800
00:33:03,640 --> 00:33:05,120
with interest included.

801
00:33:05,120 --> 00:33:06,240
How about this?

802
00:33:08,680 --> 00:33:09,880
Sister, we grew up together.

803
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:11,600
Have I ever gone back on my promises?

804
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:12,360
Right?

805
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:16,160
Also, you have our contract.

806
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:17,360
We put it down in black and white.

807
00:33:17,360 --> 00:33:19,560
You won't get the short end of the stick.

808
00:33:20,320 --> 00:33:21,120
Why did you do that?

809
00:33:21,120 --> 00:33:23,000
How dare you make the decision for me!

810
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:25,680
That's just because you won't make the decision for yourself.

811
00:33:25,680 --> 00:33:27,400
Ever since you were a kid, you have been so stupid

812
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:30,080
with money that you can even smash a dent on the ground.

813
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:31,080
A dent is so boring.

814
00:33:31,520 --> 00:33:33,240
I would dig a well.

815
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:35,000
Then I will put up a notice next to the well,

816
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:35,640
saying

817
00:33:35,640 --> 00:33:37,720
don't forget to thank the one who made the well.

818
00:33:39,040 --> 00:33:41,240
But you've pushed me into the well now.

819
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:45,720
Sister, to be honest,

820
00:33:45,720 --> 00:33:47,520
I did it for your own good.

821
00:33:48,160 --> 00:33:49,600
That's my least favorite sentence.

822
00:33:50,200 --> 00:33:51,680
What do you mean by for my own good?

823
00:33:51,680 --> 00:33:53,440
Do you have any idea what I consider as good?

824
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:55,000
Getting something for nothing.

825
00:33:56,120 --> 00:33:58,320
Who said I'm getting something for nothing?

826
00:33:58,320 --> 00:33:59,080
Tell me,

827
00:33:59,080 --> 00:33:59,970
can you get me out of this?

828
00:34:00,760 --> 00:34:01,600
No.

829
00:34:06,600 --> 00:34:08,440
You make me so anxious.

830
00:34:12,639 --> 00:34:14,120
Come on.

831
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:16,199
Don't be upset, Dai Xiaoyu.

832
00:34:16,920 --> 00:34:19,120
Know that eventually, you will tell the story

833
00:34:19,120 --> 00:34:21,719
that upset you in the past with a smile.

834
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:24,679
I can't vent my anger

835
00:34:24,679 --> 00:34:25,760
even if I kick you.

836
00:34:26,199 --> 00:34:27,080
Alright.

837
00:34:27,080 --> 00:34:28,050
Kick me if you want.

838
00:34:28,050 --> 00:34:30,440
If you're cruel enough to kick a sister 
 who treats you so well,

839
00:34:30,440 --> 00:34:31,199
then do it.

840
00:34:31,199 --> 00:34:32,239
I believe you will admire my

841
00:34:32,239 --> 00:34:33,679
clever decision before long.

842
00:34:34,159 --> 00:34:34,880
Kick me.

843
00:34:35,600 --> 00:34:36,120
I will...

844
00:34:38,600 --> 00:34:40,639
Why did you slap me for real?

845
00:34:46,080 --> 00:34:47,920
The only thing you invest in is the building.

846
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:49,880
Then you have 70 percent of the shares.

847
00:34:52,679 --> 00:34:53,800
Around this place,

848
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:55,440
